I have used this site as a high school social studies teacher and graduate student,  to get information and thoughts from those of you who were there,  or weren't there.  I graduated from high school in 1975 and am a woman,  ao I was just a bit too young to have the training to go over.  I have especially been fascinated by the postings from nurses and Vietnamese-Americans,  and of course from all of you who served in a fighting capacity.  In my training as an historical economist,  I have a bit of experience with the federal budgeting process,  and the entire PBS system is under attack.  The best thing you can do is contact your congressional representative and bombard him/her with details on this forum.  Most of them have no idea this exists,  and they need to be educated.  Especially appeal to those who are on the Finance committee and its subcommittees.  Also,  give info to those congressional folks who served,  and also those who protested.  I believe if you let them know,  they will care.  Let them know how to get to these sites,  and encourage them to browse and explore.  If anyone needs help in locating information on contacting your congress people,  please e-mail me at TeeChur@aol.com.  I think this is an extremely important battle to be fought,  and you need to approach it with tenacity and passion.  Congress holds the purse strings - educate them,  so they will allocate the funds!
